column2: extreme EWM bloom- low water level- calm winds- partly cloudy- assisted by my sons Michael (9) and Connor (6)
Sunny 80F day. Owen Lettenberger helped me today. The lake seemed brown with lots of particles floating around.
Partly cloudy- ewm still really thick- scared up a blue heron near shore. My son Michael helped collect data

Cloudy with a strong South wind as storms are moving through the area. The current temperature is 46F.  Ice off was 4-20-13.  The water is brown and murky. Silver Creek flooded over the diversion this spring.
Mostly cloudy day- slight breeze- a little cooler then normal in the mid 60's.  A few more boats out fishing then normal.  My sons Michael and Connor helped me with the testing.
Mostly cloudy day- slight breeze- a little cooler then normal in the mid 60's.  A few more boats out fishing then normal.  My sons Michael and Connor helped me with the testing.
Cloudy and breezy- lots of geese and cormorants Cloudy and breezy- lots of geese and cormorants. Water is receding well after spring flooding and Silver Creek overtopping the diversion.
Beautiful weather- my son Connor helped me this time. Weeds around my dock are so thick it's very difficult even just to row.

Mostly cloudy- breezy- 65F.  My wife Jennifer and I took the kayaks around the lake to make some observations.  It got more cloudy and the temperature dropped while we are out- rain is in the forecast.  Not much for wildlife- didn't see any fish.  Water looked extremely clear. Mostly cloudy- breezy- 65F. Overcast- 67F- and humid.  Lake is very calm and the edges are still covered in filamentous algae. My son Michael helped me collect data. Spotted some small bluegills spawning near our dock.
